Name: Ascension Outreach
Notes: Contactless distribution of pre-packaged and non-perishable bags. To register for a pickup, please text FOOD to 726-879 or leave a voicemail at 212-254-8620. Pantry service will be offered on the \*\*1st and 3rd Saturdays\*\* of each month from 8:30 am to 9:30 am. We will do our best to serve all guests, both scheduled and any others during this time.  Scheduled pantry guests should arrive as close to their appointed time as possible in order to avoid clustering on the sidewalk. Everyone is asked to stay at least 6 feet apart. Others are asked to come at 8:30am and will be directed by volunteers.  Volunteers will package the food items in advance and distribute food bags to each guest.

Astor Wines & Spirits has temporarily transitioned to delivery services only because of NYC’s rapidly evolving COVID-19 public health crisis. We remain operational as an essential business.

Name: Common Ground Compost
Address:

Mailing Address: 34 3rd Ave
#173 ((THIS IS A PO BOX))
Notes:
We are offering a residential compost pickup service.  Our pickup service is a paid service, we can pick up compost weekly, bi-weekly, monthly, from Manhattan residents anywhere south of 87th street. 

We cannot re-open the free compost drop off that was stationed outside 415 E 11th St at our community garden until the City loosens the stay at home order, but we WILL reopen that as a donation-optional drop off in the future. We understand that not everyone has the capacity to, or wants to, pay for compost services. 

All the info can be found on our website: [reclaimedorganics.org/residents][1]
